\begin{definition}
Let $f: \R^n \to \R$ be a continuous function is differentiable and functions $g_1: \R \to \R$, $\ldots$, $g_n: \R \to \R$ be differentiable and continuous functions and  
\begin{align*}
    h: \R &\longrightarrow \R \\
    t &\longmapsto h(t) = f(g_1(t), g_2(t), \ldots, g_n(t))
\end{align*}
then 
\[
h'(t) = \frac{\partial g_1}{\partial h}g_1'(t) + \frac{\partial g_2}{\partial h}g_2'(t) + \ldots + \frac{\partial g_n}{\partial h}g_n'(t)
\] 
\end{definition}